<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1862] Resource leak in ResolveVisitor.isSourceNewer()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1862</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;at org.codehaus.groovy.control.ResolveVisitor.isSourceNewer(ResolveVisitor.java:296) is a resource leak:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;lastMod = source.openConnection().getLastModified();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The connection returned by openConnection() is never closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the solution is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;URLConnection conn = source.openConnection();
lastMod = conn.getLastModified();
conn.getInputStream.close();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
